# Tasks

<!--
  Trello-style task mirror. Tasks flow top-to-bottom:
    Inbox       → captured but not yet triaged
    Next Actions → triaged, ready to pick up
    Deep Work In Progress → currently being done (cap at 3 to protect focus)
    In Review / Waiting → handed off, awaiting external response
    Done        → recently completed (prune to a recent window)
    Someday/Maybe → not now, but worth keeping a pointer to

  Each task is a checkbox + bolded title + optional metadata lines.
  Suggested metadata fields:
    **Project:** <Codename from CLAUDE.md>
    **Due:** YYYY-MM-DD
    **Created:** YYYY-MM-DD
    **Waiting on:** <person or thing>
    **Link:** <url>

  Sub-checkboxes are fine for breaking a task into checkable subtasks.

  Setup: rename to `TASKS.md` and delete the example tasks below.
-->

## Inbox
- [ ] **Example: triage this task before moving it down**
  - **Created:** YYYY-MM-DD

## Next Actions
- [ ] **Example: a small, clearly-defined next step**
  - **Project:** <Codename>
  - **Due:** YYYY-MM-DD

## Deep Work In Progress
<!-- Max 3 items. If you have a 4th, demote one back to Next Actions. -->
- [ ] **Example: a focus-block-worthy piece of work**
  - **Project:** <Codename>

## In Review / Waiting
- [ ] **Example: handed off, waiting on response**
  - **Waiting on:** <Person>
  - **Since:** YYYY-MM-DD

## Done
<!-- Prune periodically; keep the last ~2 weeks. -->
- [x] **Example: a finished task**
  - **Completed:** YYYY-MM-DD

## Someday / Maybe
- [ ] **Example: an idea worth keeping but not committed to**
